This paper deals with the security and networking aspects of Tor, making it likely to belong to the categories of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) and "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a protocol for distributing bridges, which involves algorithms and data structures, making it relevant to the categories of "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) and "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of malicious attacks and provides resistance against them, which falls under the category of "cs.SY" (Systems and Control).
